<paragraph blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[169,978,1455,1474]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[169,279,1455,1474]" pageId="6">Description.</emphasis>
Body: Elongate; brown; integument shiny; vestiture yellowish pale, decumbent,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,672,1479,1498]" pageId="6">
sides parallel-sided; length 
<quantity box="[383,451,1479,1498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[516,585,1479,1498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
; PEI: 2.6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[172,977,1503,1522]" pageId="6">
<emphasis box="[172,218,1503,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6">Head</emphasis>
: convex; frontoclypeal carina region extended forward; clypeus and labrum with setae
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,978,1526,1546]" pageId="6">
semi-decumbent; labrum slightly convex, 2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[524,542,1526,1545]" pageId="6">3</emphasis>
as long as wide; antennomera 2 through 8 serrate,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[148,978,1455,1570]" box="[148,976,1551,1570]" pageId="6">
antennomere 9 exceeding pronotal posterior angles, [AP: 7-6-10-10-11-13-12-9-10-12], (
<figureCitation box="[911,964,1551,1570]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[169,208,950,969]" captionTargetBox="[211,915,196,926]" captionTargetId="figure-206@10.[208,916,194,929]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 6–13. Antenna of Alyma species. 6) A. pallipes; 7) A. ariasvillegasai; 8) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345233/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
