</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<emphasis box="[199,285,788,807]" italics="true" pageId="7">Prothorax</emphasis>
: convex medially; areolate, sides parallel; base curved; pronotal posterior angles straight; prosternal lobe bent; prosternum convex; pronotosternal lobe marginate broadly curved; pronotosternal suture sinuate; hypomeron punctate, sinuate basally, antennal groove present (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[197,236,916,935]" captionTargetBox="[293,886,195,893]" captionTargetId="figure-202@11.[293,886,194,894]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 14–21. Pronotal hypomera of Alyma species. 14) A. pallipes; 15) A. ariasvillegasai; 16) A. calafquenensis; 17) A. contulmoensis; 18) A. lawlerae; 19) A. quiriquinaensis; 20) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345235/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); prosternum at procoxae marginate, and slightly elevated; procoxal distance 2.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[907,925,859,878]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
procoxal diameter, pronotosternal spine length 0.7 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,549,883,902]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
procoxal diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<taxonomicName box="[199,282,908,927]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,282,908,927]" italics="true" pageId="7">Scutellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: U-shaped, vestiture semi-decumbent, long, yellow; mesocoxae separated by 0.3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[989,1007,907,926]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
mesocoxal diameter; posterior margin of mesosternal cavity extending posteriorly 0.4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[894,912,931,950]" pageId="7">3</emphasis>
mesocoxal diameter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[175,1007,788,1046]" pageId="7">
<emphasis box="[199,251,980,999]" italics="true" pageId="7">Elytra</emphasis>
: interstria rugulose, slightly convex; striae pitted, pits regular; interstria convex; elytral apex rounded and explanate. 
<emphasis box="[441,473,1003,1022]" italics="true" pageId="7">Leg</emphasis>
: yellowish brown; tarsomere 4 almost similar in length to tarsomere 1, [TP: 25-19-18-23-15], (
<figureCitation box="[490,555,1027,1046]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[169,208,833,852]" captionTargetBox="[148,979,195,810]" captionTargetId="figure-203@12.[148,980,194,811]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 22–28. Tarsi of Alyma species. 22) A. pallipes; 23) A. ariasvillegasai; 24) A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5345237" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5345237/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
